Preheat your oven to 180°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #large saucepan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft and golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once the onion is cooked add @korma curry paste{50%g}, @ground cumin{1%tsp} and half the garlic. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%tin} with the @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp} and a splash of water. Add the chickpeas, half of the @nigella seeds{1%tsp}, half the @mango chutney{40%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a pinch of @sugar{} if you have some. Simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once thickened, tip the tomato mixture into a wide #baking dish{} and make a well with the back of a spoon for each egg (2 eggs per person). Crack an @eggs{4.5} into a #small bowl{} and tip into one of the wells. Repeat with the remaining eggs then scatter over the remaining nigella seeds. Bake on the middle shelf, until the eggs are cooked to your liking, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} into a small bowl and add the remaining mango chutney. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, stir and set aside. Pop half the coriander, remaining garlic and oil into a small bowl. Stir and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop the @plain naans{2} on a #baking tray{}, then evenly spread the coriander garlic oil onto the naans with a back of a #spoon{}, set aside. About 4 mins before the eggs are cooked, pop the naans onto a baking tray and bake until warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Divide the baked eggs between plates and scatter over the remaining coriander. Serve with the naans and yoghurt alongside. Enjoy!